acaman Darcy\n| valign=\"Tradi-Modern\" |\n*'''Bernice - Iwacu'''\n**Spoks Man \u2013 Burundi\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82; width=50%\" |Best Dancer Group\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82; width=50%\" |Best Radio Presenter\n! style=\"background:#EEDD82; width=50%\" |Best Gospel Artist/Group\n|-\n| valign=\"Best Dancer Group\" |\n**TBA\n**KOD\n**BKM\n**Abirabure\n**Dream Team\n**Force 257\n*'''Arakara Team'''\n| valign=\"Best Radio Presenter\" |\n**Jean Patrick Kivodo\n*'''Ami Pro'''\n**Adrian Lavista\n**Eddyson\n**Judie-caelle\n| valign=\"Gospel\" |\n*'''Prince Mshindi'''\n**GN\n**MTC\n**SMS\n**Best Muzik\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|http://www.bujaawards.com}}\n\n[[Category:Burundian music]]\n[[Category:African music awards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup|reason=2019 specific awards should be split off from this page if it has its own page|date=January 2020}}\n{{short description|Burundian music awards show}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name           = Buja Music Awards\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| current_awards = Buja Music Awards 2019\n| description    = Outstanding achievements in the [[music industry]] of [[Burundi]]\n| presenter      = [[Kora Entertainment]], Gahungu Movement\n| country        = Burundi\n| network        = \n| year           = {{Start date and age|7 july 2019}}\n| website        = {{url|bujaawards.com}}\n}}\n'''Buja Music Awards''' is a Burundian music awards show. The award established in 2018 by Kora Entertainment and Gahungu Movement to honour Burundian musicians and music producers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://plugtimes.com/2019/05/buja-music-awards-2019-nominees/|title=Buja Music Awards 2019 Nominees Announced - Full List|date=May 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nBurundian music is currently gaining global recognition at a rapid pace following this trend,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ppbdi.com/index.php/extras/sports/12789-musique-buja-music-awards|title=MUSIQUE> Buja Music Awards|website=