{"title_page": "Miss Erica", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{short description|Burundian singer (b. 1993)}}{{More citations needed|date=January 2019}}{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Miss Erica\n| background      = solo_singer\n| image           =\n| image_size      = 300px\n| alt             =\n| caption         = \n| birth_name      = Irakoze Erica\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|df=y|1993|12|3}}\n| birth_place     = {{nowrap|[[Bujumbura]], [[Burundi]]}}\n| genre           = [[African popular music|Afro pop]], [[hiplife]], [[R&B]], [[dancehall]]\n| occupation      = Singer\n| years_active    = {{nowrap|2011\u2013present}}\n| label    = Empire Avenue\n| associated_acts = [[Sat-B]], [[Best Life Music]], Gaga Blue, Sumi Crazy, Vampino, Rabadaba\n| website         = \n}}\n\n'''Irakoze Erica''',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicinafrica.net/fr/directory/miss-erica|title=Miss Erica|date=3 July 2018|website=Music in Africa|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref> (stage name '''Miss Erica)''', is a Burundian Singer-songwriter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.howwe.biz/MissErica|title=Miss Erica Music, Songs, Videos, Mp3 Downloads and biography|website=Howwe.biz|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nFrom Burundian and Rwandan parents Miss Erica grew up in [[Kigali]]. She embarked on a musical career after high school.\n\n==Career==\nShe made her musical debut in 2011 as a member of the Kora Entertainment label in collaboration with [[Best Life Music]]. In 2016 Miss Erica formed a duo with Lacia and collaborated on a song with Burundian Superstar [[Sat-B]] titled \"Joto\".\n\nMany of her earlier songs were in the dancehall genre but Miss Erica surprised her following with highlife song \"Angalia\" in July 2017, featuring Kiwundo artists [[Vampino]], [[Rabadaba]], Diplomate and Milly. Other songs in her repertoire, including \"Buziraherezo\", \"Give me love\" and \"Mon Amour\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inyarwanda.com/inkuru/85569/miss-erica-umuhanzikazi-wicyamamare-i-burundi-ukorera-muzika-ye-mu-rwanda-yashyize-hanze-a-85569.html|title=Miss Erica umuhanzikazi w'icyamamare i Burundi ukorera muzika ye mu Rwanda yashyize hanze amashusho y'indirimbo ye \"Mon amour\"-VIDEO |last=Nsengiyumva|first=Emmy|website=Inyarwanda.com|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://akeza.net/musique-miss-erica-ou-la-volonte-de-conquerir-le-coeur-des-burundais/|title=Musique : Miss Erica ou la volont\u00e9 de conqu\u00e9rir le c\u0153ur des burundais|website=Akeza.net|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n=== Singles ===\n*\"Nkundira\" rmx ft Gaga Blue and Frank Duniano\n*\"Ndatashe\" Iwacu ft [[Sat-B]]\n*\"Tell me\"\n*\"Give me love\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.howwe.biz/song/7775/give-me-lavo/1560/miss-erica|title=Miss Erica \u2022 GIVE ME LAVO \u2022 Free .MP3 Download|website=Howwe.biz|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n*\"Joto\" ft Lacia x [[Sat-B]]\n*\"Buziraherezo\"\n* \"Angalia\" \u2013 all Stars Kiwundo\n*\"Impanvu\" ft Sumi Crazy\n*\"Mon Amour\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kamerurbain.com/east-africas-best-female-artist-miss-erica-releases-mon-amour/|title=East Africa's Best Female Artist Miss Erica releases 'Mon Amour'|first=Kamer|last=Urbain|date=15 November 2018|website=Kamerurbain.com|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n*Sinovako\n*In My Heart ft [[Sat-B]]<ref>https://www.alltalkradio.net/miss-erica-in-my-heart-ft-sat-b/</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n===[[Buja Music Awards]]===\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n|Mon Amour\n|Song Of The Year\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n|Mon Amour\n|Best R&B/Afro Song\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n|\n|Best Female Artist\n|{{win}}\n|-\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n|Mon Amour\n|Video Of The Year\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n===[[Afrimusic Song Contest]]===\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2020\n|Miss Erica / In My Heart\n|Afrimusic Song Contest 2020 winner\n|{{pending}}\n|-\n{{end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Burundian singers]]\n[[Category:Burundian women]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{short description|Burundian singer (b. 1993)}}{{More citations needed|date=January 2019}}{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Miss Erica\n| background      = solo_singer\n| image           =\n| image_size      = 300px\n| alt             =\n| caption         = \n| birth_name      = Irakoze Erica\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|df=y|1993|12|3}}\n| birth_place     = {{nowrap|[[Bujumbura]], [[Burundi]]}}\n| genre           = [[African popular music|Afro pop]], [[hiplife]], [[R&B]], [[dancehall]]\n| occupation      = Singer\n| years_active    = {{nowrap|2011\u2013present}}\n| label    = [[Empire Avenue (record label)|Empire Avenue]]\n| associated_acts = [[Sat-B]], [[Best Life Music]], Gaga Blue, Sumi Crazy, Vampino, Rabadaba\n| website         = \n}}\n\n'''Irakoze Erica''',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicinafrica.net/fr/directory/miss-erica|title=Miss Erica|date=3 July 2018|website=Music in Africa|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref> (stage name '''Miss Erica)''', is a Burundian Singer-songwriter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.howwe.biz/MissErica|title=Miss Erica Music, Songs, Videos, Mp3 Downloads and biography|website=Howwe.biz|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nFrom Burundian and Rwandan parents Miss Erica grew up in [[Kigali]]. She embarked on a musical career after high school.\n\n==Career==\nShe made her musical debut in 2011 as a member of the [[Kora Entertainment]] label in collaboration with [[Best Life Music]]. In 2016 Miss Erica formed a duo with Lacia and collaborated on a song with Burundian Superstar [[Sat-B]] titled \"Joto\".\n\nMany of her earlier songs were in the dancehall genre but Miss Erica surprised her following with highlife song \"Angalia\" in July 2017, featuring Kiwundo artists [[Vampino]], [[Rabadaba]], Diplomate and Milly. Other songs in her repertoire, including \"Buziraherezo\", \"Give me love\" and \"Mon Amour\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inyarwanda.com/inkuru/85569/miss-erica-umuhanzikazi-wicyamamare-i-burundi-ukorera-muzika-ye-mu-rwanda-yashyize-hanze-a-85569.html|title=Miss Erica umuhanzikazi w'icyamamare i Burundi ukorera muzika ye mu Rwanda yashyize hanze amashusho y'indirimbo ye \"Mon amour\"-VIDEO |last=Nsengiyumva|first=Emmy|website=Inyarwanda.com|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://akeza.net/musique-miss-erica-ou-la-volonte-de-conquerir-le-coeur-des-burundais/|title=Musique : Miss Erica ou la volont\u00e9 de conqu\u00e9rir le c\u0153ur des burundais|website=Akeza.net|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n=== Singles ===\n*\"Nkundira\" rmx ft Gaga Blue and Frank Duniano\n*\"Ndatashe\" Iwacu ft [[Sat-B]]\n*\"Tell me\"\n*\"Give me love\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.howwe.biz/song/7775/give-me-lavo/1560/miss-erica|title=Miss Erica \u2022 GIVE ME LAVO \u2022 Free .MP3 Download|website=Howwe.biz|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n*\"Joto\" ft Lacia x [[Sat-B]]\n*\"Buziraherezo\"\n* \"Angalia\" \u2013 all Stars Kiwundo\n*\"Impanvu\" ft Sumi Crazy\n*\"Mon Amour\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kamerurbain.com/east-africas-best-female-artist-miss-erica-releases-mon-amour/|title=East Africa's Best Female Artist Miss Erica releases 'Mon Amour'|first=Kamer|last=Urbain|date=15 November 2018|website=Kamerurbain.com|accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n*Sinovako\n*In My Heart ft [[Sat-B]]<ref>https://www.alltalkradio.net/miss-erica-in-my-heart-ft-sat-b/</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n===[[Buja Music Awards]]===\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n|Mon Amour\n|Song Of The Year\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n|Mon Amour\n|Best R&B/Afro Song\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n|\n|Best Female Artist\n|{{win}}\n|-\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n|Mon Amour\n|Video Of The Year\n|{{nom}}\n