 as to why the title was never published in recent years.<ref name=\"NGF22a\"/><ref name=\":0\"/><ref name=\"NGF23\"/><ref name=\":1\"/> Though a prototype cartridge is rumored to exist, no [[ROM image]] of the title has managed to surface online.<ref>{{cite web|author=Shou|url=http://forums.gamengai.com/viewtopic.php?f=2&t=553&p=28471&hilit=Success+Neo+Geo#p28471|title=The emulation thread... (Page 19)|website=gamengai.com|date=June 28, 2016|access-date=2020-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200121012747/http://forums.gamengai.com/viewtopic.php?f=2&t=553&p=28471&hilit=Success+Neo+Geo|archive-date=2020-01-21|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Neo Geo}}\n{{Portal bar|1990s|Japan|Video games}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:QP (video game)}}\n<nowiki>[[Category:1997 video games]]\n[[Category:Cancelled arcade games]]\n[[Category:Cancelled Neo Geo games]]\n[[Category:Cancelled Neo Geo CD games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Party video games]]\n[[Category:Success (company) games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring female protagonists]]</nowiki>\n", "name_user": "KGRAMR", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QP_(video_game)"}
